reviews.review_text: great show/great quality I just downloaded a torrent of this show (same source) and it's great.  really nice quality for the time and PigPen singing "Run Rudolph Run" is a lot of fun

Pigpen I'm only on Truckin', but I can't remember hearing Pigpen so high in the mix since '67 or '68. RIP Ron and Jerry.

Later...Casey Jones is great, even with a slight mix-up. Bobby (I assume) announcing the break and the beginning of Ramble missing. And someone needs to be reminded that Cryptical, Drums and The Other One are really ONE SONG. To hear the two track changes between those three parts destroys the continuity, the mood, the high. So in this respect, our old vinyl, cassettes and reels (more than 40 years old!) are superior to what we have here. Should that be? Is that progress? And yet, still five stars.
- Great parts; generally a pretty average show.
